  "target_response": {
    "text": "You slept 6.5 hours last night, an hour short of your sleep need of 7.5 hours. Your 7-day average sits at 6.9 hours, so this is a pattern rather than a one-off — you're carrying a steady nightly shortfall, which is exactly what waking up tired feels like. The good news is your wake time barely moves, so the lever is the front end: pull bedtime earlier by about 25 minutes this week — that alone closes most of the nightly gap — and protect the last half hour before bed from screens so the earlier time actually sticks. Hold that for a week, then judge it by whether the 7-day average climbs toward your need, not by any single night.",
